extends layout

block content
  section.page-heading
    p.eyebrow About
    h1 About FocusFlow
    p.lead A small productivity dashboard that feels smart without using real AI.

  section.about-grid
    article.card
      h2 Project
      p
        | FocusFlow helps students and busy users decide what to work on next.
        | It uses a clear scoring system to rank tasks instead of calling an AI model.
      p
        | The goal is to keep the project realistic, understandable, and easy to explain.

    article.card
      h2 What It Does
      ul.simple-list
        li Add, edit, delete, and complete tasks.
        li Save tasks in localStorage so they stay in the browser.
        li Show the top priority task and the top 3 ranked tasks.
        li Display weather after the user enters a city.
        li Recommend books based on the highest ranked category.
        li Run a simple focus timer for study sessions.

    article.card
      h2 APIs
      ul.simple-list
        li Geoapify Geocoding API converts a city into coordinates.
        li Open-Meteo Weather API returns current weather details.
        li Open Library API searches books related to the top task category.
